#compdef bundown
# =============================================================================
# bundown — Rysana AI's "Fast all-in-one Markdown runtime and
#           bundler, built on Bun" — a Bun-native CLI that
#           EXECUTES code blocks INSIDE markdown files as a
#           runtime AND BUNDLES code blocks across markdown
#           into source-tree directories.  Distinguishing from
#           runme (similar markdown-as-script tool), nbexec
#           (Jupyter notebook runner), and other literate-
#           programming tools by:
#             - BUN-NATIVE — built specifically for the Bun
#               JavaScript runtime; uses Bun.file / Bun.write /
#               Bun.semver / Bun.CryptoHasher internally
#             - EXECUTE-FROM-MARKDOWN: `bundown run app.md`
#               executes every code block in app.md sequentially,
#               with shared state across blocks (each block can
#               see the previous block's variables)
#             - EXECUTE-FROM-URL: `bundown run https://example.
#               com/app.md` fetches + executes a remote markdown
#               file directly — no clone, no build, no install
#             - EXECUTE-FROM-DIR: `bundown run app/` walks the
#               directory, finds .md files, executes them
#             - SYNC BIDIRECTIONAL: `bundown sync app.md app/`
#               UNPACKS code blocks from markdown into individual
#               files in a directory; `bundown sync app/ app.md`
#               PACKS files from a directory back into a single
#               markdown file with code blocks
#             - PER-BLOCK FLAGS: code blocks can carry inline
#               flags like `--os linux` (only run on Linux),
#               `--tag deploy` (filter by tag), `-f path/to/
#               file.ext` (link block to a file path)
#             - --tag FILTERING: `bundown run --tag deploy
#               app.md` runs only blocks tagged `--tag deploy`
#             - UPGRADE SUBCOMMAND: `bundown upgrade` updates to
#               the latest version (Bun-style)
#             - PRETTY-PRINTED SOURCE during execution via
#               --print flag (uses emphasize for code highlighting)
#             - WRAP-ANSI for terminal text wrapping of usage +
#               help + per-block output
#           Used by: Bun developers writing executable runbooks
#           in markdown, technical writers shipping live-runnable
#           documentation, AI agents generating literate
#           workflows, and as the headline showcase of Bun-
#           native CLI design.
#
# Author:  Rysana AI (rysana-ai organization on GitHub) — startup
#          building AI-native developer tools.  bundown released
#          2024; active development through 2026 with regular
#          releases.
# Source:  https://github.com/rysana-ai/bundown
#          https://github.com/rysana-ai/bundown/blob/main/bundown/bundown.ts
#          https://github.com/rysana-ai/bundown/blob/main/bundown/ui.ts
# CLI:     bundown/bundown.ts — hand-rolled argument parser via
#          parseArgs() function that walks argv looking for
#          known flags + subcommands.  Headline library:
#          **wrap-ansi** (chalk + emphasize + string-width are
#          well-documented across many Node completions — wrap-
#          ansi is the new variant being documented here,
#          completing Axis 12 three-language symmetry).
# Library: wrap-ansi (https://github.com/chalk/wrap-ansi)
#          ("wrap-ansi" — Sindre Sorhus / chalk organization —
#           released 2014 as "Wordwrap a string with ANSI
#           escape codes" — the dominant Node.js library for
#           terminal text wrapping with ANSI awareness.
#           Distinct from word-wrap (older, NOT ansi-aware),
#           wordwrap (similarly older), cli-truncate (truncate
#           not wrap), and slice-ansi (slice not wrap) by being:
#             1. ANSI-ESCAPE-AWARE WRAPPING — every chunk
#                preserves opening + closing ANSI escapes
#                across wrapped lines; styles never bleed across
#                line breaks
#             2. WIDE-CHARACTER AWARE — uses string-width to
#                compute VISIBLE width for CJK / emoji / wide
#                glyphs (mirrors textwrap R625 + reflow R626's
#                approach)
#             3. SINDRE-SORHUS / CHALK ECOSYSTEM CITIZEN — part
#                of the chalk org alongside chalk (the dominant
#                Node coloring library), string-width, strip-
#                ansi, ansi-styles, ansi-regex; all transitively
#                used by chalk
#             4. ZERO RUNTIME DEPENDENCIES (in modern v9+):
#                pure JS implementation using string-width
#                (chalk-org companion)
#             5. CHALK-FOUNDATIONAL — transitively used by every
#                Node CLI that depends on chalk + yargs + listr2
#                + ora + oclif + Inquirer + thousands of other
#                packages
#             6. CONFIGURABLE OPTIONS:
#                  * hard (boolean) — true = also break on words
#                                       longer than the column;
#                                       false (default) = leave
#                                       long words intact
#                  * trim (boolean) — true (default) = trim
#                                       leading whitespace from
#                                       wrapped lines; false =
#                                       preserve
#                  * wordWrap (boolean) — true (default) = wrap at
#                                            word boundaries;
#                                            false = wrap at column
#                                            even mid-word
#             7. CHALK ORG COMMUNITY MAINTENANCE — wrap-ansi is
#                under chalk/wrap-ansi on GitHub (formerly
#                Sindre's personal repo) — community-maintained)
# License: MIT (bundown); MIT (wrap-ansi)
# Status:  bundown — 213+ stars on rysana-ai/bundown; wrap-ansi —
#          138+ stars on chalk/wrap-ansi BUT ~3.5 BILLION WEEKLY
#          NPM DOWNLOADS (transitively via chalk), one of the
#          TOP-10 MOST-DOWNLOADED NPM PACKAGES OF ALL TIME.
#          Foundational dependency of vadimdemedes/ink (38k
#          stars) + snyk/cli + storybookjs/storybook + marp-team/
#          marp-cli (3.6k stars) + listr2 + oclif/core + expo/
#          expo (49k stars) + chalk (transitively) + yargs/cliui
#          + apify/apify-cli + slicknode/slicknode + rysana-ai/
#          bundown (THIS) + hundreds of thousands of Node CLIs
#          (basically every npm package that produces colored
#          terminal output).
#
