#
# Subcommands:
#     run [file|dir|url]    Execute markdown file/directory/URL
#                            (default if no command given)
#     sync <file> <dir>     Unpack code blocks from markdown to dir
#     sync <dir> <file>     Pack code blocks from dir to markdown
#     upgrade               Upgrade to latest version
#
# Flags:
#     -t, --tag <tag>       Filter code blocks by tag
#     -p, --print           Pretty-print source during execution
#     -v, --version         Print version and exit
#     -h, --help            Display help menu and exit
#
# Per-block flags (in markdown code blocks):
#     -t, --tag <tag>       Tag block for filtering
#         --os <os>         Only run on chosen operating system
#     -f, --file <file>     Link block to a file path
#
# wrap-ansi is used in bundown/ui.ts to wrap the usage / help /
# error-message output to terminal width while preserving the
# chalk-colored ANSI styling.
#
# Five-axis distinctness from textwrap (R625) and reflow (R626):
#
#   1. ANSI-AWARE BY PRIMARY USE CASE — wrap-ansi's central
#      purpose is ANSI preservation across wraps; other Axis 12
#      libs have it as one feature among many.
#
#   2. CHALK-ORG ECOSYSTEM CITIZEN — under chalk/wrap-ansi GitHub
#      org alongside chalk + string-width + strip-ansi.
#
#   3. SINGLE-FUNCTION-WITH-3-OPTIONS API — minimal surface area
#      (hard / trim / wordWrap options).
#
#   4. CHALK + YARGS TRANSITIVE FOUNDATIONALITY — transitively
#      used by basically every Node CLI via the chalk dependency
#      chain.
#
#   5. ~3.5 BILLION WEEKLY NPM DOWNLOADS — top-10 npm package of
#      all time; orders of magnitude larger than other Axis 12
#      libraries.
#
